name: Ally Mind
desc: A high-performance unit developed to enhance the Artificial Intelligence program of the Allies of Justice. Loaded with elements collected from a meteor found in the Worm Nebula, it allows for highly tuned processing. But its full capacity is not yet determined.

name: Ally of Justice Cosmic Gateway
desc: If your opponent controls 2 or more monsters, including a LIGHT monster, you can Special Summon this card from your hand.

name: Ally of Justice Enemy Catcher
desc: When this card is Normal Summoned, you can take control of 1 face-down Defense Position monster your opponent controls, until the End Phase of this turn.

name: Ally of Justice Field Marshal
desc:
1 Tuner + 2 or more non-Tuner monsters
This card cannot be Special Summoned except by Synchro Summon. When this card attacks a face-down Defense Position monster, destroys it by battle, and sends it to the Graveyard, draw 1 card.

name: Ally of Justice Nullfier
desc: Any LIGHT monster that has battled this card has its effects negated (starting after damage calculation).

name: Ally of Justice Reverse Break
desc: If a face-up LIGHT monster is on the field, destroy this card. If this card attacks a face-down Defense Position monster, destroy that monster immediately with this card's effect without flipping it face-up or applying damage calculation.

name: Ally of Justice Searcher
desc: Once per turn, you can discard 1 card to select 1 face-down Defense Position monster your opponent controls and change it to face-up Attack Position. Flip Effects are not activated at this time.

name: Ally of Justice Thunder Armor
desc: This card cannot be Special Summoned. During the battle between an attacking "Ally of Justice" monster you control and a Defense Position monster whose DEF is lower than the ATK of the attacking monster, inflict the difference as Battle Damage to your opponent.

name: Ally of Justice Unlimiter
desc: You can Tribute this card to select 1 face-up "Ally of Justice" monster you control. Double its original ATK until the End Phase.

name: Dai-sojo of the Ice Barrier
desc: When this card is Normal or Flip Summoned, it is changed to Defense Position. Face-up "Ice Barrier" monsters you control cannot be destroyed by Spell or Trap Card effects.

name: Dewloren, Tiger King of the Ice Barrier
desc:
1 Tuner + 1 or more non-Tuner WATER monsters
Once per turn, you can return any number of face-up cards you control to the owner's hand. For each card returned to the owner's hand by this effect, this card gains 500 ATK until the End Phase.

name: Fabled Gallabas
desc: You can discard 1 card to the GY, then target 1 monster your opponent controls with DEF less than or equal to this card's ATK; destroy that target.

name: Fabled Grimro
desc: If you control a "Fabled" monster: You can send this card from your hand to the GY; add 1 "Fabled" monster from your Deck to your hand, except "Fabled Grimro".

name: Fabled Kushano
desc: If this card is in your GY: You can discard 1 "Fabled" monster to the GY, except "Fabled Kushano"; add this card to your hand.

name: Fabled Lurrie
desc: If this card is discarded to the GY: Special Summon it.

name: Fabled Valkyrus
desc:
1 "Fabled" Tuner + 1+ non-Tuner monsters
Once per turn: You can discard 1 Fiend monster; draw 1 card.

name: Flamvell Baby
desc: During your Main Phase, you can send this card from your hand to the Graveyard to select 1 face-up FIRE monster you control and have it gain 400 ATK.

name: Flamvell Grunika
desc: When this card destroys a monster by battle and sends it to the Graveyard, inflict damage to your opponent equal to the Level of the destroyed monster x 200.

name: Genex Army
desc: When this card is Tribute Summoned by Tributing a "Genex" monster, you can destroy 1 card your opponent controls.

name: Genex Blastfan
desc: When this card is Special Summoned, you can add 1 DARK "Genex" monster from your Deck to your hand.

name: Genex Doctor
desc: You can Tribute 1 face-up "Genex Controller" to select and destroy 1 card on the field.

name: Genex Furnace
desc: If you control a face-up "Genex Controller", you can Normal Summon this card without Tributing.

name: Genex Gaia
desc: If this card would be destroyed, you can destroy 1 "Genex Controller" monster you control instead.

name: Genex Recycled
desc: Once per turn, you can select 1 "Genex" monster in your Graveyard. Until the End Phase, this card's name is treated as the selected monster's name.

name: Genex Solar
desc: You can Normal Summon this card by Tributing 1 "Genex" monster. Inflict 500 damage to your opponent each time a face-up "Genex" monster you control is sent to the Graveyard.

name: Genex Spare
desc: Once per turn, if you control another "Genex" monster, you can make this card's name "Genex Controller" until the End Phase.

name: Genex Turbine
desc: All face-up "Genex" monsters you control gain 400 ATK.

name: Geo Genex
desc:
"Genex Controller" + 1 or more non-Tuner EARTH monsters
Once per turn, if you control a face-up Level 4 or lower "Genex" monster(s), you can switch the original ATK and DEF of this card until the End Phase, for as long as you control a face-up Level 4 or lower "Genex" monster(s).

name: Geomancer of the Ice Barrier
desc: Discard 1 card and declare 1 Attribute. This card cannot be selected as an attack target by monsters with that Attribute. This effect can only be used once while this card is face-up on the field.

name: Jurrac Giganoto
desc:
1 Tuner + 1 or more non-Tuner Dinosaur-Type monsters
All face-up "Jurrac" monsters you control gain 200 ATK for each "Jurrac" monster in your Graveyard.

name: Jurrac Monoloph
desc: This card can attack all monsters your opponent controls once each.

name: Jurrac Protops
desc: This card gains 100 ATK for each monster your opponent controls.

name: Jurrac Tyrannus
desc: You can Tribute 1 Dinosaur monster; this card gains 500 ATK. If this card destroys an opponent's monster by battle and sends it to the GY: This card gains 300 ATK.

name: Jurrac Velo
desc: When this face-up Attack Position card attacks or is attacked, and it is destroyed by battle and sent to the Graveyard, you can Special Summon 1 "Jurrac" monster with 1700 or less ATK from your Deck.

name: Medium of the Ice Barrier
desc: If your opponent controls 4 or more cards than you do, you can Special Summon this card (from your hand). Your opponent can only activate 1 Spell/Trap Card each turn.

name: Mist Valley Apex Avian
desc: Once per chain, when a card or effect is activated (Quick Effect): You can target 1 "Mist Valley" card you control; return that target to the hand, and if you do, negate the activation, and if you do that, destroy it.

name: Mist Valley Baby Roc
desc: When this card is sent directly from the hand to the Graveyard, you can Special Summon it.

name: Mist Valley Executor
desc: When this card is Normal Summoned, return all face-up Spell and Trap Cards on the field to their owners' hands.

name: Mist Valley Falcon
desc: This card cannot declare an attack unless you return 1 card you control to the hand.

name: Mist Valley Thunder Lord
desc:
1 Tuner + 1 or more non-Tuner "Mist Valley" monsters
Once per turn, you can select 1 card you control. Return it to the hand, and this card gains 500 ATK until the End Phase. This effect can be activated during either player's turn.

name: Naturia Antjaw
desc: When your opponent Special Summons a monster(s), you can Special Summon 1 Level 3 or lower "Naturia" monster from your Deck.

name: Naturia Beast
desc:
1 EARTH Tuner + 1+ non-Tuner EARTH monsters 
When a Spell Card is activated (Quick Effect): You can send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the GY; negate the activation, and if you do, destroy it. This card must be face-up on the field to activate and to resolve this effect.

card_sets.set_name: Premium Gold: Return of the Bling

name: Naturia Beetle
desc: Switch the original ATK and DEF of this card each time a Spell Card is activated.

name: Naturia Cosmobeet
desc: When your opponent Normal Summons or Sets a monster, you can Special Summon this card from your hand.

name: Naturia Guardian
desc: When your opponent Normal Summons a monster, this card gains 300 ATK until the End Phase.

name: Naturia Leodrake
desc: 1 EARTH Tuner + 1 or more non-Tuner EARTH monsters

name: Naturia Rock
desc: When a Trap Card is activated, you can send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard to Special Summon this card from your hand.

name: Naturia Rosewhip
desc: Your opponent can only activate 1 Spell/Trap Card per turn.

name: Naturia Spiderfang
desc: This card cannot declare an attack unless your opponent activated a Spell, Trap, Spell/Trap effect, or Monster effect this turn.

name: Naturia Vein
desc: You can Tribute this card and 1 "Naturia" monster to negate the activation of your opponent's Spell or Trap Card, and destroy it.

name: Pilgrim of the Ice Barrier
desc: This card cannot be destroyed by battle with a monster with 1900 or more ATK.

name: Thermal Genex
desc:
"Genex Controller" + 1 or more non-Tuner FIRE monsters
This card gains 200 ATK for each FIRE monster in your Graveyard. If this card destroys an opponent's monster by battle, inflict 200 damage to your opponent for each "Genex" monster in your Graveyard.

name: Windmill Genex
desc:
"Genex Controller" + 1 or more non-Tuner WIND monsters
This card gains 300 ATK for each face-down Spell and Trap Card on the field. You can send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard to select and destroy 1 face-down Spell or Trap Card.

name: Worm Linx
desc: FLIP: During each End Phase, if this card is face-up, draw 1 card.

name: Worm Millidith
desc: FLIP: You can equip this card to a monster your opponent controls as an Equip Card. Inflict 400 damage to the controller of the equipped monster during each Standby Phase.

name: Worm Noble
desc: FLIP: If this card is flipped face-up by an opponent's monster's attack, inflict damage to your opponent equal to half the attacking monster's ATK.

name: Worm Opera
desc: FLIP: All face-up monsters on the field lose 500 ATK, except Reptile-Type "Worm" monsters.

name: Worm Prince
desc: If this card destroys an opponent's monster by battle, you can add 1 Reptile-Type "Worm" monster from your Deck to your hand. Destroy this card during the End Phase if you do not control another Reptile-Type "Worm" monster.

name: Worm Queen
desc: You can Tribute Summon this card in face-up Attack Position by Tributing 1 Reptile-Type "Worm" monster. Once per turn, you can Tribute 1 Reptile-Type "Worm" monster to Special Summon 1 Reptile-Type "Worm" monster from your Deck with a Level less than or equal to the Tributed monster.

name: Worm Rakuyeh
desc: This card can only declare an attack the turn it was flipped face-up. If this card attacks, it is changed to face-down Defense Position at the end of the Battle Phase.
